values:
worries that were once worries are non existant 
and desires that once were are no longer
i feel happy. no more searching. what i wanted is now here... but is it what i really do want? sometimes i scare myself and say no... but then the other time i think that what is right now actually is right. but i wonder for how long it will be right. i don't like thinking about prolonged time. time scares me a little. no- not time- trying to have set plans scares me. who knows where i'll be years from now- emotionally and physically. yet, i don't care to know. i want it to come at me in its own way. experience is something i want... in almost everything. i want to see things that i will not always get to see. i want to love being young. i never thought i would BE in love when i was young. i'm sure of this. i really do love him. i love most things about him. i love his sweetness and how he says stupid shit. i love how he calls me sexy when all i do is kiss him. the way he kisses me on the forehead when he's standing above me never seems to fail at grabbing my joy either. the stupid things he does no longer affects me- it only makes me continue to love him. but when we talk about the length of our relationship, things get rocky. he likes to think about the future and what's coming. i don't.

everything is interesting like this.
if i thought thoughts didn't stop before, now they're wild.
on top of that, i'm a kid again.
i'm reminded of my summers in massachusetts during my youth.
i could just see my uncle's house around me.
i was really in my kitchen as a 16 year old,
but i felt 8 years old.
i'm reminded of how "recently" we played old maid.
i'd never really played it before then.
but everything i do now,
i'm doing it at my uncle's house... but i'm really doing everything in my own home.
broad memories of my uncle's old house:
the time when my aunts and my mother were cooking lobster, and my aunt sarah let the lobster walk around the kitchen... and i came in scared to death.

all the legos we'd play with...

a little game we used to call "gooser"

aladin (the 2nd one... return of jafar?) in the little room in that house.

lego island in that room on the slowest computer imaginable...

the secret hiding place in one of the stairs...

i miss that house... it was so much fun. it was pretty big too.
but when i was high today i couldn't stop being at that house.
it's weird, sometimes when i'm high, i become a kid again. i love the feeling. i can't get rid of it either... like everything i think about always comes back to the tiem of being a kid.

annoying but whatever i'll be okay.


in other news--- i've decided i'm going to become very into the CF walk this year.
i really want to get people from our school to come!!
and not that there are many people on here that i know but if you didn't know, my cousin has CF.
CF is short for Cystic Fibrosis.
basically, what it is, is a disease inherited from your parents. [if the trait is carried by one or both of your parents.]
when you have CF, you have this defective gene and its protein product causes the body to produce
a thick mucus that the lungs cannot break down so it eventually will clog the lungs.
this protein product also takes away the body's natural ability to break down and absorb food
[that basically means- they cannot gain weight as easy as most people can so they have to eat fattening food and a lot of it to maintain a normal weight]


that is the basic summerization of this disease that my 5 year old cousin has.
the walk is May 20th starting & ending at playland. PLEASE PLEASE PLEASE- if you think you may be able to do it please tell me!! i'd love to get ATLEAST 3 people from our school [besides me and my family] to walk... and maybe more.

with your help i can. =]
oh yeah btw- the median age for my cousin's life is 37.
i would love to see her live longer than that.
it is my lifetime goal to raise enough awareness of the disease and try to find a cure.
any questions- ask me. =]
